:INFO
The Book That Corrects What We Think We Know
Almost everything the public believed about Columbine in the years after 1999 \
was wrong. Dave Cullen spent ten years reporting, reviewing documents, and \
interviewing survivors and investigators to write a book that dismantles the \
myths systematically and replaces them with something harder and more accurate. \
The killers were not loners. They were not bullied. They were not targeting \
any specific social group. The book does not offer the simple story. \
It offers the true one.

